  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\nSupport raw mode OSD on LV-backed PVC. Although OSD on PVC uses raw mode, LV-backed PVC still use LVM mode.\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\n\r\nIt can simplify OSD management in many ways and can avoid many problems that come from LVM. For example, in OSD on LV-backed PVC, which uses LVM mode OSD, LV's tag may be updated from both host and container simultaneously. The former is from admin in the host, the latter is from Rook/Ceph container to add Ceph-related tags. As a result, LVM metadata may corrupt.\r\n\r\nAdded(Aug 31, 2020):\r\nFore more detail, please refer to the following document.\r\nhttps://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/Documentation/ceph-common-issues.md#lvm-metadata-can-be-corrupted-with-osd-on-lv-backed-pvc",
